valhalla-wasm
=============

The build scripts, the Embind wrapper (src/valhalla_worker.cpp), the browser
routing worker (web/), and the tile-building reference scripts (scripts/) in this
repository are licensed under the MIT License (see LICENSE), Copyright (c) 2025
rivers.run.

This project builds and redistributes third-party software:

- Valhalla (https://github.com/valhalla/valhalla) — the C++ routing engine that
  is compiled to WebAssembly here. Valhalla is licensed under the MIT License,
  Copyright (c) Valhalla contributors. The compiled artifacts (valhalla.js,
  valhalla.wasm) are derived works of Valhalla and its dependencies.

- The build links several C++ libraries fetched via vcpkg at build time
  (protobuf, sqlite3, libcurl, zlib, lz4, abseil, boost, rapidjson, date,
  cxxopts). Each is distributed under its own license; consult the respective
  upstream projects.

- Tiles are built using the public Docker image
  ghcr.io/gis-ops/docker-valhalla, which packages the upstream Valhalla CLI
  tools.

Pinned upstream references used to produce the committed prebuilt artifacts are
recorded in versions.lock.
